=== Noun ===
'''{{PAGENAME}}''' ([[ごおん]], ''goon'')

# The pronunciation of Chinese hanzi characters used in the Wú ([[吳]] or [[吴]]) and Yuè ([[越]]) regions of China.  

# A category of ''on'yomi'' ([[音読み]], おんよみ), the Japanese approximation of the original Chinese pronunciation.  
#: The kanji pronunciation first brought to Japan via Korea.  This category was called ''waon'' ([[和音]], わおん) until the middle of the Heian period, after which it was also called ''goon''.  Generally regarded as the character reading brought over long ago from the lower reaches of the [[Yangtze]] River (the Wú region).  
#: Contrast with ''kan'on'' ([[漢音]]), ''sōon'' ([[宋音]]), and ''tōon'' ([[唐音]]).  

